# 🤖 JARVIS - Voice Controlled Browser AI Agent

> "Just A Rather Very Intelligent System" - Inspired by Iron Man

A fully local, free, voice-controlled browser agent. Speak commands naturally and Jarvis controls your browser, searches the web, plays YouTube, reads Wikipedia and more.

---

## 🎯 What Jarvis Can Do

| Command | Action |
|---|---|
| "Search for AI news on Google" | Opens Google with results |
| "Play lofi music" | Opens YouTube and plays it |
| "Tell me about Elon Musk" | Reads Wikipedia summary |
| "What's the weather in Chicago" | Shows weather on Google |
| "Show me maps of New York" | Opens Google Maps |
| "Open Reddit" | Opens any website by voice |
| "Search latest songs on YouTube" | Searches YouTube |

---

## 🏗️ Architecture
```
Your Voice
    ↓
Whisper / Google STT (voice input)
    ↓
Ollama Llama 3.2 (intent understanding)
    ↓
Intent Router (what action to take)
    ↓
Playwright (browser control)
    ↓
pyttsx3 (voice response)
```

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- **Voice Input** - SpeechRecognition + Google STT
- **AI Brain** - Ollama + Llama 3.2 (100% local, free)
- **Browser Control** - Playwright (Chromium)
- **Voice Output** - pyttsx3 (offline TTS)
- **Wikipedia** - wikipedia-api
- **Memory** - In-session conversation history
- **Backend** - Python 3.11

---

## 📁 Project Structure
```
jarvis/
├── main.py                 # Entry point
├── config/
│   └── settings.py         # Configuration
├── core/
│   ├── voice_input.py      # Listens to your voice
│   ├── voice_output.py     # Speaks responses
│   ├── brain.py            # AI intent understanding
│   └── intent_router.py    # Routes commands
├── skills/
│   └── wikipedia_skill.py  # Wikipedia search
├── memory/
│   └── context_store.py    # Conversation memory
└── browser/
    └── controller.py       # Playwright browser control
```

---

## 🚀 Setup

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.10+
- Ollama installed
- 8GB+ RAM

### Installation
```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/vvasireddi/jarvis.git
cd jarvis

# Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate  # Windows
source venv/bin/activate  # Mac/Linux

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Install Playwright browser
playwright install chromium

# Pull Ollama model
ollama pull llama3.2
```

### Run
```bash
python main.py
```

